annotationA: P53 protein long form variant 1; P53 is a transcriptional factor required for adaptive responses to genotoxic stress, including cell death, compensatory proliferation and DNA repair
annotationB: Cdk5 activator-like protein (Cdk5alpha) is the sole, essential stimulatory subunit for the Cdk5 kinase. The Cdk5/Cdk5alpha complex is active in post-mitotic neurons. It is required for synaptic homeostasis and fidelity of axon patterning, and altered activity causes adult-onset neurodegeneration
